    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for spirv-tools, vulkan-loader, vulkan-headers, vulkan-validation-layers, vulkan-tools.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The vulkan packages contain the reference ICD loader and validation layers for\nVulkan, a graphics and compute API for cross-platform access to modern GPUs.\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* Rebase vulkan-loader in 8.6 (BZ#2016391)\n\n* Rebase vulkan-headers in 8.6 (BZ#2016392)\n\n* Rebase spirv-headers in 8.6 (BZ#2016393)\n\n* Rebase spirv-tools in 8.6 (BZ#2016394)\n\n* Rebase vulkan-tools in 8.6 (BZ#2016395)\n\n* Rebase vulkan-validation-layers in 8.6 (BZ#2016396)\n\n* Rebase glslang in 8.6 (BZ#2027693)\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
